data.content:
Create `.vscode/mcp.json` with this content:

```json
{
  "servers": {
    "MyMcpServer": {
      "type": "stdio",
      "command": "dotnet",
      "args": ["run", "--project", "src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj"]
    }
  }
}
```

Then in VS Code:
1. Open **Copilot Chat** → switch to **Agent** mode
2. Click the **wrench icon** (Select Tools) → verify your server and tools appear
3. Ask a prompt that triggers your tool and approve execution

**If tools don't appear:** run `dotnet build` first, then restart the MCP server. Also verify your tool classes have `[McpServerToolType]` and methods have `[McpServerTool]`.

> **Note:** If your server uses HTTP transport (has a `ModelContextProtocol.AspNetCore` package reference), use `"type": "http"` with `"url": "http://localhost:<port>"` instead.
